records.addlTxt:
9:57 AM; Case called for Plea/sentencing hearing. Defendant Samuel J Weber in court.  Attorney Luis Daniel Gutierrez in court for Samuel J Weber.  Prosecuting attorney Christian Farina in court for the State of Wisconsin. Court note a plea questionnaire has been filed and recites the offer as listed in the document.  State and Defense confirm the offer.  Court conducts plea colloquy with the defendant.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 2, Court finds defendant guilty of Count 2.  Court orders Count 1 be dismissed and read in.

Sentencing arguments made by the State.
Victim A presents statements.
Sentencing arguments made by Atty. Gutierrez.


COUNT 2: 
The Court Orders the Following:

Withheld sentence (Court will award 1 Day Credit IF defendant is revoked and sentenced)

Term of Probation: 1 Year

Conditions of Probation:
-	Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
-	Follow any conditions deemed appropriate by Agent;
-	No violent contact with Victim(s) listed in the Criminal Complaint.
-	Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.'s;
-	No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
-	No Use or Possession of CBD products;
-	No use or possession of any controlled substances without a valid doctor's prescription
-	No use of possession of vaping products;
-	Follow all rules set at home by the Defendant's parents;
-	Take Thinking for a Change Course;
-	Make best efforts to Maintain/Obtain part time employment, full time schooling, or a combination of the two;
-	Complete 20 Hours of Community Service;  
-	Defendant is not to possess any dangerous weapons.

Condition Time: 30 Days STAYED to be used at the Agents discretion (Huber privileges at the Agent's discretion)

COSTS:  $100.00 (DV surcharge ONLY, all other costs waived by the Court);

DNA Surcharge: $200.00;

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

Total costs/fine/forfeiture:  to be paid as a condition of probation. Failure to pay;  will result in a civil judgment.

**Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all restitution/costs/fees, and no new law violations, and obtains High school Diploma. If the Defendant violates any terms of his/her probation, or has any condition time imposed, the Court will deem that the conditions precedent necessary for the conditional grant of Expunction have not been met and therefore Expunction is denied. The defendant shall file a petition with the Court to verify the successful completion of the sentence.**
